cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the design and evaluation of CNN architectures for facial affect analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the implementation of a music recommendation interface based on predicted user affect, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper evaluates user satisfaction with the interface, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes three variants of established CNN architectures, which involves optimization and model selection, and thus falls under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses a large dataset for evaluation, which involves data processing and analysis, and thus falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
